WEBVTT

00:02.394 --> 00:03.985
<i> Previously on</i> Monarch...

00:04.005 --> 00:06.063
♪<i> You broke my heart</i> ♪

00:06.232 --> 00:09.491
♪<i> My body and mind.</i> ♪

00:09.510 --> 00:11.343
-You stole mama's song!
-You mean before you could?

00:11.420 --> 00:13.512
Of course you helped Mama die.

00:13.663 --> 00:15.330
<i> You're just like her.</i>

00:15.407 --> 00:18.242
Wade, you got a song for me?

00:18.260 --> 00:20.077
My style does tend more
towards the, uh...

00:20.095 --> 00:22.354
Lovesick young cowboy?

00:22.581 --> 00:24.672
Jamie Burke,
producer out of Atlanta.

00:24.841 --> 00:25.749
Yeah, charmed.

00:25.842 --> 00:27.267
JAMIE:
Nicky, you're so talented.

00:27.361 --> 00:29.269
I want you to know it really is

00:29.421 --> 00:31.363
a pleasure meeting you.

00:31.515 --> 00:33.848
I feel terrible doing this
to Gigi.

00:33.868 --> 00:35.367
<i> LUKE:</i>
<i>That's what you said last time.</i>

00:35.519 --> 00:37.536
<i> NICKY:</i>
<i> How far along are you?</i>

00:37.687 --> 00:39.112
Luke doesn't even know yet.

00:39.265 --> 00:41.098
Dottie was being blackmailed.

00:41.191 --> 00:43.767
$50,000 a month, every month.

00:43.769 --> 00:45.377
You tell 'em that Albie Roman

00:45.604 --> 00:47.629
ain't paying 'em another cent.

00:48.698 --> 00:50.591
♪ ♪

00:56.057 --> 00:57.431
(car alarm chirps)

01:15.301 --> 01:17.242
♪ ♪

01:38.507 --> 01:40.490
(line rings, clicks)

01:40.509 --> 01:43.251
It's done.

01:43.345 --> 01:44.311
(beeps)

01:45.106 --> 01:47.564
(engine starts)

02:00.937 --> 02:03.080
♪ ♪

02:18.305 --> 02:20.955
Pretty as the day
I first met you.

02:21.049 --> 02:23.392
You are too sweet.

02:26.388 --> 02:28.397
Come on, sugar.

02:38.308 --> 02:39.733
WOMAN:
Right in there.

02:39.851 --> 02:41.735
-(door opens)
-MARTY: Thank you.

02:41.811 --> 02:44.496
I got here as quick
as I could.

02:44.648 --> 02:47.240
Any luck figuring out
who these blackmailers are?

02:47.393 --> 02:49.910
Like I said, they're pros.

02:50.004 --> 02:53.154
Communication's airtight.
End-to-end encryption,

02:53.174 --> 02:54.989
asymmetric algorithms.

02:55.009 --> 02:56.341
In English.

02:56.493 --> 02:59.178
They're ciphers.
Impossible to trace.

02:59.329 --> 03:00.904
(sighs)

03:01.073 --> 03:02.848
Then I want you
to set up a meeting.

03:02.999 --> 03:04.074
What? No, Albie...

03:04.092 --> 03:06.092
I want to meet
these vultures in person.

03:06.245 --> 03:08.353
And look 'em in the eye.

03:09.748 --> 03:11.690
They're gonna pay
for the pain they caused her.

03:11.917 --> 03:14.175
Albie, I don't think
you understand.

03:14.195 --> 03:16.102
These people are dangerous.

03:16.255 --> 03:18.846
Here's
what you don't understand.

03:18.941 --> 03:21.491
So am I.

03:27.524 --> 03:30.450
Excuse me, what are
you doing in here? Hey!

03:30.602 --> 03:32.211
Clive!

03:32.362 --> 03:34.120
Well, I'm making a ginger
and turmeric smoothie.

03:34.273 --> 03:35.863
They say it improves your mood.

03:35.958 --> 03:38.458
Well, it is certainly
not improving mine.

03:38.610 --> 03:41.202
Do you think two weeks in
the guest house is gonna, like,

03:41.255 --> 03:42.537
make me forget who you are?

03:42.706 --> 03:44.798
Actually, the time apart's
been quite the revelation.

03:44.950 --> 03:46.800
See, we all knew
that your mother

03:46.952 --> 03:49.061
had terminal cancer, but, uh...

03:49.288 --> 03:52.289
I always wondered...

03:52.458 --> 03:55.459
how she passed so quickly.

03:55.552 --> 03:57.236
And now I know.

03:57.463 --> 03:58.812
You killed her.

03:58.906 --> 04:01.073
I did not kill her.

04:01.300 --> 04:03.133
And I have the proof.

04:03.226 --> 04:06.411
Oxycodone, Nick,
which you gave to her, no doubt.

04:07.581 --> 04:10.398
I helped her open the bottle
is what I did.

04:10.492 --> 04:11.733
That's a distinction
known only to you, me,

04:11.752 --> 04:12.826
and Dottie-- God rest her soul.

04:12.995 --> 04:14.569
What do you want?

04:14.663 --> 04:15.979
Penthouse suite,

04:15.998 --> 04:17.739
200 grand walking-around money.

04:17.833 --> 04:19.407
Ah, to start.

04:19.426 --> 04:22.152
Are you insane?
It's what she wanted.

04:22.154 --> 04:23.503
Or maybe you wanted
to be Queen of Country

04:23.597 --> 04:25.580
just a little bit sooner
than Dottie was ready

04:25.749 --> 04:28.141
to relinquish the crown.

04:34.699 --> 04:36.525
♪ ♪

04:43.933 --> 04:45.692
(Gigi groans)

04:45.844 --> 04:47.602
It's hot as hell.

04:47.621 --> 04:49.270
Somebody please remind me
why we shoot

04:49.364 --> 04:52.291
the<i> Roman Family Christmas</i>
special in July again?

04:52.367 --> 04:54.851
ALBIE:
You know why. 'Cause Christmas

04:54.962 --> 04:56.295
was your mama's
favorite holiday,

04:56.446 --> 04:58.130
and this way she could
have it twice a year.

04:58.281 --> 05:01.258
And so a Roman tradition
was born.

05:02.469 --> 05:04.194
Fake Christmas.

05:04.212 --> 05:06.546
Which brings us
to why we're all here.

05:06.640 --> 05:09.549
We are gonna be filming the
special all week, and viewership

05:09.718 --> 05:10.809
has been a little off lately.

05:10.960 --> 05:13.219
No kidding.
This show is so dated.

05:13.388 --> 05:15.129
All we're missing is VCRs

05:15.223 --> 05:17.707
and "Re-elect Reagan" spots.

05:17.726 --> 05:20.301
It may be old-fashioned,
but Mama loved tradition, so...

05:20.470 --> 05:22.379
You know what else Mama liked?
Ratings.

05:22.397 --> 05:24.806
So why don't we bring this show

05:24.825 --> 05:27.308
into the 21st century?
You know, maybe update it

05:27.328 --> 05:30.645
-for the under-80 crowd.
-Spoken like a true millennial.

05:30.664 --> 05:32.889
Are you two still mad
at each other over the rodeo?

05:32.908 --> 05:35.058
-I'm not mad at her.
-Why would she be?

05:35.077 --> 05:36.560
She's the one
who stole my song.

05:36.653 --> 05:38.670
And now
it's number one on Spotify.

05:38.822 --> 05:39.838
Technically, it was Mama's song.

05:39.989 --> 05:41.731
Technically, you're a thieving,

05:41.825 --> 05:43.233
backstabbing bitch.

05:43.251 --> 05:45.569
Good, this is just
that Christmas spirit I love.

05:45.587 --> 05:47.471
Enough.

05:48.907 --> 05:51.591
This special is a tradition
that your mama loved.

05:51.685 --> 05:53.410
But, Daddy, everyone knows

05:53.428 --> 05:56.096
-you never liked it.
-But your mama did.

05:56.248 --> 05:58.690
Half of a marriage
is partnership.

05:58.842 --> 06:01.101
And the other half...

06:01.269 --> 06:02.919
is keeping your mouth shut.

06:03.012 --> 06:05.513
I'll see y'all at the studio.

06:05.607 --> 06:09.242
(country version
of "Away in a Manger" playing)

06:17.360 --> 06:19.711
(groans)
Look at me.

06:21.123 --> 06:23.048
Is this really
the image that you want

06:23.199 --> 06:26.051
for one of Monarch's
hottest up-and-coming acts?

06:26.128 --> 06:27.611
You look adorable.

06:27.779 --> 06:29.036
That's what the fans want.

06:29.114 --> 06:30.964
Do you even know
who my fans are?

06:31.058 --> 06:33.967
They're single moms
and lesbians.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.619
They don't care about adorable.

06:35.637 --> 06:37.454
They want honest and real.

06:37.472 --> 06:39.973
Geeg, I don't know why you
complain about this every year.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.234
-It's...
-It's tradition, yeah, I know.

06:42.403 --> 06:44.569
Just like toxic masculinity
and the Confederacy.

06:46.055 --> 06:48.573
<i> CARINEH:</i>
<i> You're really not gonna like</i>
<i> what Clive's done now.</i>

06:48.650 --> 06:50.725
NICKY:
Unbelievable.

06:50.744 --> 06:53.078
I-I call him out for cheating,
and then...

06:53.229 --> 06:55.321
he's the hot stud
and I'm, what am I?

06:55.474 --> 06:59.233
I'm, oh, I'm pathetic
and I can't move on.

06:59.253 --> 07:01.402
-Who is she?
-Some young skank. Who cares?

07:01.496 --> 07:04.256
You need to show your fans
you've moved on

07:04.407 --> 07:06.149
right now.

07:06.168 --> 07:08.818
-I mean, you have.
-You mean Wade?

07:08.912 --> 07:11.412
That's just...
It was just some fling.

07:11.432 --> 07:12.914
I'm not judging you, sweetie.

07:12.933 --> 07:15.267
But there's a double standard.
I mean,

07:15.494 --> 07:18.161
Clive can whore it up all over
town and his stock goes up.

07:18.330 --> 07:21.773
You need to...
bravely open yourself up

07:21.925 --> 07:23.683
to a new relationship.

07:23.760 --> 07:25.335
Something people can root for.

07:25.428 --> 07:28.596
Go public as a couple with Wade.

07:28.674 --> 07:30.173
But we're not a couple.

07:30.266 --> 07:31.783
And the Romans aren't
the perfect family

07:31.893 --> 07:34.286
that sit around the fire
and sip eggnog

07:34.437 --> 07:36.121
and sing "Frosty the Snowman."

07:36.348 --> 07:38.439
But people want to believe
what they want to believe.

07:38.533 --> 07:40.200
So...

07:40.352 --> 07:42.202
You, what, you want me to go...

07:42.354 --> 07:44.612
out on a fake date?

07:44.631 --> 07:45.964
As your publicist, I think

07:46.115 --> 07:48.041
you and Wade
will keep you exciting,

07:48.193 --> 07:50.635
yet still wholesome
and aspirational.

07:50.787 --> 07:52.362
As your friend, I know
that you and Wade will give

07:52.455 --> 07:54.121
Clive a taste
of his own medicine.

07:54.216 --> 07:56.216
-I'll think about it.
-Well, don't think too long.

07:56.310 --> 07:57.867
Clive is probably making out
with at least

07:57.869 --> 07:59.686
one of the Kardashians
as we speak.

08:01.315 --> 08:04.691
♪ ♪

08:14.161 --> 08:17.245
Where the hell are they?

08:18.907 --> 08:21.500
They ain't coming.

08:24.505 --> 08:28.131
Everybody's a badass
till they ain't.

08:36.908 --> 08:39.017
♪ ♪

09:01.950 --> 09:04.543
<i> NICKY: Listen, I know we're all</i>
<i>busy with the Christmas special,</i>

09:04.694 --> 09:06.402
but we need to talk.

09:06.404 --> 09:08.605
My sister may be
a giant pain in the ass

09:08.698 --> 09:11.716
who hates my guts right now,
but I am not...

09:11.943 --> 09:13.718
gonna sit quietly
in the background

09:13.870 --> 09:15.628
when her entire future

09:15.781 --> 09:18.114
with the only woman she ever
loved hangs in the balance

09:18.133 --> 09:20.058
Nicky, I love her, too.

09:20.285 --> 09:22.043
-We all do.
-Right, because

09:22.062 --> 09:23.620
nothing says I love you more

09:23.622 --> 09:25.230
than sleeping
with the brother-in-law.

09:25.381 --> 09:27.882
Listen, this wasn't
some sordid affair.

09:27.901 --> 09:29.809
All right, there are
real feelings here.

09:29.961 --> 09:32.053
Yeah, but it was
a mistake, obviously.

09:32.072 --> 09:34.798
We're deeply sorry
for it and it's done.

09:34.816 --> 09:36.241
Good, because right now we have

09:36.318 --> 09:38.484
a much bigger problem
that's harder to hide.

09:38.579 --> 09:40.412
A baby.

09:40.563 --> 09:42.305
Yeah, well, Gigi and I have been
wanting another one, so...

09:42.398 --> 09:44.231
I know, which leads me to why

09:44.251 --> 09:45.825
I invited you both here,
because I think

09:45.902 --> 09:49.312
I might have a solution that,
that suits all of us.

09:49.331 --> 09:52.649
So listen up
and keep an open mind.

09:52.667 --> 09:55.260
<i> ("Deck the Halls" playing</i>
<i> on piano)</i>

10:00.583 --> 10:03.417
Oh, "Deck the Halls,"
how original.

10:03.511 --> 10:05.345
Psst.

10:05.497 --> 10:06.938
Yay.

10:07.165 --> 10:08.773
What brings you by here?

10:08.925 --> 10:10.108
This is such a surprise.

10:10.259 --> 10:12.259
What, I need an excuse
to come visit my wife?

10:12.279 --> 10:15.447
Oh, I see, you want something.

10:15.523 --> 10:17.507
-I get it.
-No.

10:17.525 --> 10:19.175
I just, um...

10:19.194 --> 10:21.769
I've been thinking
a lot about our plan...

10:21.863 --> 10:23.346
to have another baby.

10:23.365 --> 10:24.530
Really?

10:24.683 --> 10:26.182
Right now?

10:26.201 --> 10:28.317
I know it sounds crazy,

10:28.319 --> 10:30.962
but since we decided I'd carry,

10:31.114 --> 10:33.022
what if we fast-track
this whole thing

10:33.041 --> 10:35.449
and ask Luke to be our donor?

10:35.543 --> 10:37.710
Luke? My brother?

10:37.863 --> 10:40.029
Chiseled CEO

10:40.048 --> 10:41.881
with a daddy complex Luke?

10:41.975 --> 10:43.383
I know, I...

10:43.535 --> 10:45.793
Well, what made you think
of him?

10:45.887 --> 10:47.704
It's common to ask a relative
or a close friend.

10:47.722 --> 10:49.205
Okay, but

10:49.298 --> 10:50.798
I'm not sure if having

10:50.892 --> 10:53.134
another baby right now
is a great idea.

10:53.228 --> 10:55.970
I-I'm trying to light a fire
under my career.

10:56.064 --> 10:57.730
Why the rush?

10:57.899 --> 10:59.899
We have all the time
in the world.

11:00.051 --> 11:01.718
MAN:
Gigi, we need you on set.

11:01.736 --> 11:03.569
-Got to go.
-Oh. Bye.

11:03.722 --> 11:05.664
Bye, honey.

11:10.578 --> 11:12.245
I guess
when you're rich and famous,

11:12.397 --> 11:14.414
you're allowed to have
two Christmases.

11:14.508 --> 11:16.900
Amazing.

11:16.902 --> 11:18.659
Mom.

11:18.753 --> 11:21.179
-Is that Wade Stellings?
-It is.

11:21.330 --> 11:23.907
I told you
everybody would be here.

11:23.925 --> 11:26.333
And now you are, too.
(laughs)

11:26.353 --> 11:27.394
Hey, there.

11:29.005 --> 11:30.747
You ready to pretend
it's Christmas?

11:30.765 --> 11:32.582
Hi.

11:32.600 --> 11:33.692
It's, um...

11:33.919 --> 11:36.194
It's good to see you again.

11:40.258 --> 11:42.425
It is, but now I believe

11:42.444 --> 11:44.160
we're late
for our wardrobe fitting.

11:46.856 --> 11:48.206
This isn't the junior prom.

11:48.433 --> 11:50.375
We're here for one reason
and one reason only.

11:50.602 --> 11:51.710
To work.

11:51.861 --> 11:54.045
Not to meet cute boys.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.611
-Bye.
<i> -Roman Family Christmas</i>

12:01.704 --> 12:04.038
has been Stellings family
viewing since I was little.

12:04.207 --> 12:06.891
My mama called it
"comfort food for the soul."

12:07.043 --> 12:09.043
She can't believe
I'm a guest star.

12:09.062 --> 12:10.544
We're lucky to have you.

12:10.564 --> 12:12.439
Maybe next time
you'll ask me yourself.

12:14.401 --> 12:16.735
All right, so this isn't
about the Christmas special.

12:16.886 --> 12:19.645
You didn't have to have our
publicists arrange another date.

12:19.740 --> 12:22.574
You could have just asked.
I mean, I have seen you naked.

12:22.801 --> 12:24.391
Yeah, and it was fun.

12:24.560 --> 12:26.652
But I'm not
a one-night-stand kind of girl.

12:26.805 --> 12:29.989
That's why my publicist reached
out-- it's a fake date, PR.

12:30.066 --> 12:31.991
I'm not here for fake anything.

12:32.143 --> 12:34.252
All right, why are you here?

12:34.403 --> 12:36.329
For you.

12:36.481 --> 12:38.131
Bye.

12:41.577 --> 12:43.553
Thank you.

12:46.508 --> 12:48.349
All right.

12:52.255 --> 12:53.563
Hi.

12:54.666 --> 12:55.857
You doing okay?

12:57.185 --> 12:59.685
I know Fake Christmas isn't
the same without Mama.

12:59.854 --> 13:02.171
Nothing's the same without Mama.

13:02.265 --> 13:03.973
What's wrong, Daddy?

13:04.025 --> 13:07.452
Well, it's like this.
Your mother...

13:07.679 --> 13:09.454
she was being blackmailed.

13:09.623 --> 13:11.864
What? How do you know that?

13:12.017 --> 13:14.183
Marty.

13:14.202 --> 13:15.868
Said it'd been going on
for the...

13:15.945 --> 13:17.462
better part
of the last ten years.

13:17.689 --> 13:19.689
Well, I don't understand.

13:19.707 --> 13:21.691
Wh-Who? And why?

13:21.709 --> 13:23.860
"Who" is on my to-do list.

13:23.878 --> 13:25.804
But "why"?

13:26.031 --> 13:28.640
I think she was protecting me.

13:30.626 --> 13:31.976
My affair.

13:32.128 --> 13:33.719
You know,
the one I told you about.

13:33.872 --> 13:35.146
That was years ago.

13:35.298 --> 13:36.297
Somebody must've known.

13:36.374 --> 13:37.631
And you know your mother.

13:37.651 --> 13:40.151
The Roman image was
important to her,

13:40.303 --> 13:42.803
at... at any expense.

13:42.897 --> 13:44.489
I don't think that was it.

13:45.808 --> 13:48.809
The night Mama passed,
she said something to me.

13:48.829 --> 13:51.478
I've done things
that can never

13:51.647 --> 13:54.390
be forgiven.

13:54.483 --> 13:56.075
I didn't know...

13:56.227 --> 13:58.837
what it meant.
I-I still don't, but...

13:59.064 --> 14:01.397
it wasn't about you.

14:01.416 --> 14:03.716
I think Mama may have
secrets of her own.

14:16.414 --> 14:19.599
Another lump of coal
for you, Gigi.

14:19.751 --> 14:21.417
That's okay, Nicky.

14:21.436 --> 14:24.011
<i> 'Cause coal turns</i>
<i> into diamonds.</i>

14:24.030 --> 14:26.089
<i> And like Mama always said,</i>

14:26.091 --> 14:28.091
<i> your luck is what you make it.</i>

14:28.093 --> 14:31.035
<i> -And Mama turned her luck...</i>
-Ridiculous.

14:31.262 --> 14:34.980
They're grown women now.

14:35.133 --> 14:37.600
(laughs):
Oh, don't, don't be a grinch.

14:37.619 --> 14:40.027
They're helping people
feel better about their lives.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.529
We're the first family
of country music.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.290
And that's degrading.

14:44.442 --> 14:46.626
Look, all right, I know you
never had any of this

14:46.720 --> 14:48.111
when you were growing up.

14:48.204 --> 14:49.721
You had no Christmas,
no music...

14:49.948 --> 14:52.373
no love.

14:52.450 --> 14:55.376
But even though our girls
are out there pretending,

14:55.470 --> 14:56.728
the audience,

14:56.897 --> 14:59.046
what they're feeling is real.

14:59.065 --> 15:02.125
Real love, real joy.

15:02.143 --> 15:05.219
Just what I feel every morning
when I wake up with you.

15:05.313 --> 15:08.072
Now don't you think
everybody is entitled

15:08.224 --> 15:09.741
to have just
a little bit of that?

15:09.968 --> 15:12.059
What would I be without you?

15:12.153 --> 15:14.078
Oh, you'd be fine.

15:14.230 --> 15:16.897
And you're never gonna have
to find out because

15:16.917 --> 15:19.709
I'm always gonna be with you.

15:22.830 --> 15:24.923
<i> NICKY:</i>
<i> And Mama turned her luck</i>

15:25.074 --> 15:27.817
into a lot of diamonds.

15:27.835 --> 15:29.910
Mm-hmm.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.578
Cut!

15:31.656 --> 15:33.080
Check it.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.581
Hey, Geeg?

15:34.601 --> 15:36.676
Do not follow me.

15:36.828 --> 15:39.753
Or I'm gonna show you where
to shove that lump of coal.

15:39.847 --> 15:41.105
All right, well,
I need to talk to you.

15:41.332 --> 15:45.001
Please, I need
my best friend right now.

15:45.094 --> 15:46.110
I have a fake date
with Wade Stellings.

15:46.262 --> 15:48.095
-Say what now?
-It's to show everybody

15:48.189 --> 15:49.781
that I'm moving on.

15:50.008 --> 15:51.932
You've done worse for the press.

15:52.010 --> 15:53.934
Just treat it
like a work dinner.

15:54.028 --> 15:56.846
Yep. I slept with him.

15:56.864 --> 15:59.682
Oh.

15:59.701 --> 16:01.751
Now this is getting good.

16:03.279 --> 16:05.521
-So what's the problem?
-He's a lot younger than me.

16:05.540 --> 16:07.781
And I don't even know
who I am with a man anymore.

16:07.801 --> 16:10.134
Would you stop thinking
for once?

16:10.286 --> 16:12.303
Geez Louise! Just go have fun.

16:12.455 --> 16:15.381
Nobody deserves that
more than you do.

16:15.533 --> 16:16.882
Really?

16:17.035 --> 16:18.977
Really.

16:19.128 --> 16:22.480
You're still a sneaky,
conniving bitch, though.

16:27.136 --> 16:29.988
Gigi says now's not
the right time for another baby.

16:30.215 --> 16:32.448
And you know how she is.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.384
Yeah, of course I know
how she is.

16:35.403 --> 16:36.643
She's a Roman.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.237
She's set in her ways.

16:38.389 --> 16:40.164
Well, every day I'm getting
closer to showing.

16:40.391 --> 16:42.834
I mean, there is something
we haven't talked about.

16:42.985 --> 16:44.393
What?

16:44.412 --> 16:46.487
I mean, Nicky has
no say over us.

16:46.506 --> 16:48.397
There is no us, Luke.

16:48.416 --> 16:50.416
That's what I'm saying,
there could be.

16:50.510 --> 16:52.401
No, there can't.

16:52.403 --> 16:54.737
You are my brother-in-law.
And I am in love

16:54.830 --> 16:56.088
with your sister.

16:56.182 --> 16:57.573
We were a mistake.

16:57.666 --> 16:59.666
And-and at this rate,

16:59.761 --> 17:01.352
next week's<i> Jerry Springer.</i>

17:02.580 --> 17:03.688
You're serious?

17:03.857 --> 17:05.839
You really think that plan
of Nicky's is gonna work?

17:05.933 --> 17:07.266
It is ridiculous.

17:07.418 --> 17:10.753
At this point,
it's the only hope I've got.

17:10.772 --> 17:12.864
So if you care about me,

17:12.940 --> 17:16.159
please help me hold
onto the life I want...

17:17.686 --> 17:19.037
...with Gigi.

17:23.692 --> 17:26.461
♪ ♪

17:29.698 --> 17:32.275
(laughter)

17:32.293 --> 17:34.034
Um, thank you for dinner.

17:34.054 --> 17:35.444
Hey, I had fun.

17:35.463 --> 17:37.037
Thank you.

17:37.057 --> 17:39.706
And since our publicists
set it up,

17:39.801 --> 17:41.225
it's a tax write-off.

17:41.452 --> 17:42.560
(laughs)

17:42.787 --> 17:45.137
Nicky, I've been crushing
on you for years.

17:45.231 --> 17:48.124
I even had your poster up
in my dorm room.

17:48.126 --> 17:49.901
I used to fantasize about...

17:49.977 --> 17:51.736
Yeah, you can stop right there.

17:51.887 --> 17:53.720
...singing with you

17:53.815 --> 17:56.407
-one day.
-(giggles)

17:58.486 --> 18:00.136
Hey...

18:00.229 --> 18:02.062
no disrespect
to your marriage, but...

18:02.082 --> 18:03.989
I always hoped
you'd be single someday.

18:04.142 --> 18:05.658
(chuckles)

18:05.810 --> 18:07.401
I don't know what to say.

18:07.495 --> 18:08.978
Well...

18:09.147 --> 18:11.631
say you'll do a song with me.

18:14.335 --> 18:15.927
Okay.

18:16.154 --> 18:17.653
(chuckles)

18:17.672 --> 18:20.264
(crowd cheering)

18:20.416 --> 18:22.325
You ready?

18:22.343 --> 18:23.492
Thank you.

18:23.661 --> 18:25.344
Nicky Roman,
ladies and gentlemen.

18:25.496 --> 18:27.688
(Lady A's "Need You Now"
playing)

18:31.502 --> 18:33.002
Hey, I'm honored.

18:33.020 --> 18:34.195
Let's hear it.

18:35.782 --> 18:38.507
♪<i> Picture perfect memories</i> ♪

18:38.526 --> 18:42.411
-♪<i> Scattered</i>
<i> all around the floor</i> ♪
-Oh, yeah.

18:45.441 --> 18:47.291
♪<i> Reaching for the phone</i>
<i> 'cause</i> ♪

18:47.518 --> 18:51.003
♪<i> I can't fight it anymore</i> ♪

18:52.948 --> 18:55.115
BOTH:
♪<i> And I wonder</i> ♪

18:55.135 --> 18:59.428
♪<i> If I ever cross your mind</i> ♪

19:01.290 --> 19:03.624
NICKY:
♪<i> For me it happens</i> ♪

19:03.792 --> 19:06.644
♪<i> All the time</i> ♪

19:06.795 --> 19:08.980
♪<i> It's a quarter after one</i> ♪

19:09.207 --> 19:11.149
♪<i> I'm all alone</i> ♪

19:11.300 --> 19:14.152
♪<i> And I need you now</i> ♪

19:14.303 --> 19:17.880
WADE:
♪<i> And I said I wouldn't call</i> ♪

19:17.899 --> 19:22.660
♪<i> But I'm a little drunk</i>
<i> and I need you now</i> ♪

19:24.055 --> 19:25.663
BOTH:
♪<i> And I don't know</i> ♪

19:25.814 --> 19:29.074
♪<i> How I can do without</i> ♪

19:29.227 --> 19:31.652
♪<i> I just need you</i> ♪

19:31.671 --> 19:37.550
♪<i> Now</i> ♪

19:38.511 --> 19:40.586
♪<i> I just need you</i> ♪

19:40.738 --> 19:47.092
♪<i> Now.</i> ♪

19:47.245 --> 19:50.021
-There she is.
-Thank you.

19:51.840 --> 19:53.691
(clamoring)

19:53.842 --> 19:54.859
Wicky!

19:54.936 --> 19:56.861
Well, that went viral fast.

19:57.755 --> 19:59.179
Given that they've waited
all this time in the heat,

19:59.273 --> 20:00.531
might as well give them
what they want.

20:00.758 --> 20:02.366
Well, if you insist.

20:02.593 --> 20:04.619
(whooping, cheering)

20:08.208 --> 20:09.782
I'm not that girl on the poster.

20:09.934 --> 20:11.617
Of course you are.

20:11.711 --> 20:14.128
You're exactly like
I always thought you'd be.

20:16.883 --> 20:19.091
(cheering, clamoring)

20:24.799 --> 20:27.207
Everybody's shipping "Wicky."

20:27.301 --> 20:29.301
You'll be on next week's cover
for sure.

20:29.470 --> 20:32.546
Well, you can send
18 copies to Clive.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.732
One for every single year
we were married.

20:34.883 --> 20:36.883
Well, you make the cutest elf.

20:36.903 --> 20:38.069
(chuckles)

20:38.296 --> 20:40.646
That was the best fake date
I've ever had.

20:40.798 --> 20:44.891
Hey, when you're done practicing
your solo, I'll be in my trailer

20:44.911 --> 20:47.227
later if you want to, um,

20:47.247 --> 20:50.081
roast some chestnuts
or... something.

20:50.232 --> 20:52.491
-All right.
<i> -(phone rings)</i>

20:52.568 --> 20:53.918
Hey, Mom.

20:54.145 --> 20:55.586
<i> Hey. Are you done filming?</i>

20:55.738 --> 20:57.255
Do you want me to pick you up?

20:57.482 --> 20:58.238
<i> Not yet.</i>

20:58.332 --> 20:59.757
They said we're running late.

20:59.984 --> 21:01.667
Looks like I'm gonna be here
until at least midnight.

21:01.761 --> 21:03.243
<i> Oh, okay, okay.</i>

21:03.263 --> 21:04.929
<i> Well, then call me</i>
<i> as soon as you're done.</i>

21:05.156 --> 21:06.973
I will. Love you.

21:08.268 --> 21:09.675
Hey.

21:09.769 --> 21:11.727
Almost too easy.

21:16.667 --> 21:18.985
(piano playing intro
to "Cowboy Take Me Away")

21:20.671 --> 21:22.613
♪ ♪

21:29.196 --> 21:33.291
♪<i> I said I wanna touch</i>
<i> the earth</i> ♪

21:33.442 --> 21:36.627
♪<i> I wanna break it</i>
<i> in my hands</i> ♪

21:36.779 --> 21:39.888
♪<i> I wanna grow something wild</i> ♪

21:39.990 --> 21:42.949
♪<i> And unruly</i> ♪

21:42.969 --> 21:46.137
♪<i> I wanna sleep</i>
<i> on the hard ground</i> ♪

21:46.364 --> 21:50.049
♪<i> In the comfort of your arms</i> ♪

21:50.201 --> 21:53.311
♪<i> On a pillow of blue bonnets</i> ♪

21:53.462 --> 21:56.963
♪<i> In a blanket</i>
<i> made of stars, oh</i> ♪

21:57.058 --> 21:59.650
♪<i> It sounds good</i> ♪

21:59.802 --> 22:02.153
♪<i> To me</i> ♪

22:02.304 --> 22:05.639
♪<i> I said, cowboy take me</i> ♪

22:05.658 --> 22:07.900
♪<i> Away</i> ♪

22:08.069 --> 22:10.886
♪<i> Fly this girl as high</i> ♪

22:10.979 --> 22:14.981
♪<i> As you can</i>
<i> into the wild blue</i> ♪

22:15.076 --> 22:18.985
♪<i> Set me free, oh</i> ♪

22:19.005 --> 22:21.505
♪<i> I pray</i> ♪

22:21.732 --> 22:25.009
♪<i> Closer to heaven above</i> ♪

22:25.160 --> 22:28.829
♪<i> And closer to you</i> ♪

22:28.848 --> 22:32.600
♪<i> Closer to you</i> ♪

22:33.594 --> 22:37.063
(vocalizing)

22:38.841 --> 22:42.342
♪<i> Uh-huh.</i> ♪

22:42.362 --> 22:44.528
Not enough cowboys
around anymore.

22:45.606 --> 22:47.256
Nope.

22:47.274 --> 22:49.182
You know, when I was a kid,
I dressed as a cowboy

22:49.202 --> 22:50.776
for Halloween one year.

22:50.870 --> 22:52.703
I had a lasso and everything.

22:52.855 --> 22:54.613
That's cute.

22:54.765 --> 22:56.615
You don't strike me as a cowboy.

22:56.767 --> 22:58.267
You don't strike me as someone

22:58.360 --> 23:00.252
who wants a cowboy
to take her away.

23:01.288 --> 23:03.272
Well, I'd say everybody wants

23:03.365 --> 23:05.966
a cowboy once in their life.

23:07.053 --> 23:08.794
I know your mom built
this empire

23:08.946 --> 23:11.296
on being the ideal family
and all.

23:11.391 --> 23:13.891
But you don't have
to be perfect all the time.

23:14.060 --> 23:15.784
No one is.

23:15.878 --> 23:19.230
My mama always told me
that if...

23:19.457 --> 23:21.715
you act
like everything is perfect,

23:21.734 --> 23:23.626
then...

23:23.719 --> 23:25.051
it will be.

23:25.146 --> 23:27.129
(chuckles) Don't know
if I believe her, but...

23:27.298 --> 23:29.481
Yeah, your mother was
a huge loss.

23:29.634 --> 23:31.242
For all of you
in different ways.

23:31.393 --> 23:34.136
You talking about my daddy?

23:34.229 --> 23:37.063
I've, I've...
tried my best to help him...

23:37.083 --> 23:39.083
Well, no one can be
all things to all people

23:39.234 --> 23:40.159
without any help.

23:40.311 --> 23:42.144
Have you ever heard
of Dottie Roman?

23:42.163 --> 23:43.421
Yeah, well...

23:43.572 --> 23:45.648
maybe quit worrying
about being Dottie.

23:45.666 --> 23:47.983
And just focus on being Nicky
for a change.

23:48.002 --> 23:50.169
Well, that is very easy
for you to say.

23:50.263 --> 23:52.838
Supposedly a woman has to...

23:52.990 --> 23:55.841
be it all, have it all.

23:55.935 --> 23:57.676
Not if she chooses
the right cowboy.

23:57.828 --> 23:59.770
(chuckles)
Well, you already

23:59.997 --> 24:01.847
said that...

24:01.999 --> 24:04.591
that's not me.

24:04.685 --> 24:06.669
I can take care of myself.

24:06.687 --> 24:08.170
I'm sure you can.

24:08.189 --> 24:09.688
The question is...

24:09.782 --> 24:11.323
why would you want to?

24:18.849 --> 24:21.000
(laughter)

24:21.944 --> 24:24.536
I can't believe I'm here.

24:24.630 --> 24:27.131
If my mom knew,
she'd kill us both.

24:27.282 --> 24:29.300
-Well, should I take you back?
-Are you crazy?

24:30.303 --> 24:32.619
Two weeks ago,
I was in Albuquerque

24:32.713 --> 24:34.046
studying for my chem finals,

24:34.140 --> 24:36.081
and now I'm here.

24:36.233 --> 24:37.791
With you.

24:37.810 --> 24:39.643
(laughs)

24:39.795 --> 24:41.645
I feel like Cinderella.

24:41.797 --> 24:44.523
Your home is beautiful.

24:46.393 --> 24:48.569
Your whole world is beautiful.

24:52.066 --> 24:54.307
So are you.

24:54.327 --> 24:56.368
(chuckles)

25:02.150 --> 25:04.043
(both laugh)

25:05.730 --> 25:07.988
(door opens, closes)

25:08.007 --> 25:09.632
KAYLA:
They're ready for you.

25:11.844 --> 25:13.677
Look at me.

25:14.680 --> 25:17.923
Every time I do this special,
I'm five years old again.

25:18.075 --> 25:20.926
Nicky is the perfect
pretty princess

25:21.078 --> 25:23.837
and I'm the fat gay Nutcracker.

25:23.931 --> 25:26.098
(laughs)

25:26.192 --> 25:27.841
I thought my life
had moved past this.

25:27.935 --> 25:29.585
Hey.

25:29.678 --> 25:31.028
You are my Nutcracker.

25:31.255 --> 25:32.512
Well...

25:32.606 --> 25:34.757
let's hope you still feel that
way after I go out there

25:34.850 --> 25:36.659
and make a big fool of myself.

25:37.703 --> 25:39.094
Then don't.

25:39.113 --> 25:41.113
What do you mean?

25:41.265 --> 25:43.265
Either walk off this set

25:43.284 --> 25:46.526
and tell your family
you're done being their mascot.

25:46.546 --> 25:48.620
Or you quit complaining,
you go out there

25:48.773 --> 25:51.123
and you do things your way.

25:51.275 --> 25:54.385
But either way,
you just have to be yourself.

25:55.963 --> 25:57.871
So...

25:57.965 --> 26:00.224
get cracking.

26:10.644 --> 26:13.362
(indistinct chatter)

26:14.222 --> 26:15.981
(indistinct whispering)

26:16.133 --> 26:17.499
-Okay.
-Okay.

26:17.559 --> 26:19.493
(chatter continues)

26:23.324 --> 26:25.140
Y'all been watching
Fake Christmas all week.

26:25.233 --> 26:27.400
Well, I'm fixin'
to show y'all something real.

26:27.494 --> 26:29.569
(banjo playing intro to
"Born This Way")

26:29.663 --> 26:33.148
♪<i> My mama told me</i>
<i> when I was young</i> ♪

26:33.241 --> 26:36.427
♪<i> We are all born superstars</i> ♪

26:37.504 --> 26:41.340
♪<i> She rolled my hair</i>
<i> and put my lipstick on</i> ♪

26:41.492 --> 26:44.560
♪<i> In the glass of her boudoir</i> ♪

26:46.831 --> 26:50.165
♪<i> "There's nothing wrong</i>
<i> with loving who you are</i> ♪

26:50.184 --> 26:53.018
♪<i> "'Cause he made you</i>
<i> perfect, babe</i> ♪

26:54.355 --> 26:58.006
♪<i> So hold your head up,</i>
<i> girl, and you'll go far"</i> ♪

26:58.025 --> 27:01.193
♪<i> Listen to me when I say</i> ♪

27:01.345 --> 27:05.681
♪<i> I'm beautiful in my way</i>
<i> 'cause God makes no mistakes</i> ♪

27:05.774 --> 27:08.684
♪<i> I'm on the right track, baby</i> ♪

27:08.702 --> 27:10.961
♪<i> I was born this way</i> ♪

27:14.041 --> 27:15.749
♪<i> Don't be a drag,</i>
<i> just be a queen</i> ♪

27:15.801 --> 27:18.952
♪<i> Don't be a drag, just be</i>
<i> a queen, don't be a drag</i> ♪

27:19.046 --> 27:22.514
♪<i> Just be a queen</i> ♪

27:23.550 --> 27:25.100
(Gigi whoops)

27:27.388 --> 27:29.647
(clapping)

27:29.874 --> 27:33.558
♪<i> No matter gay, straight or bi,</i>
<i> lesbian, transgender life</i> ♪

27:33.711 --> 27:37.896
♪<i> I'm on the right track, baby,</i>
<i> I was born to survive</i> ♪

27:38.048 --> 27:41.717
♪<i> I was born this way, hey,</i>
<i> I was born this way, hey</i> ♪

27:41.810 --> 27:44.662
♪<i> I'm on the right track, baby</i> ♪

27:44.889 --> 27:46.555
♪<i> I was born this</i> ♪

27:46.573 --> 27:50.084
♪<i> Way.</i> ♪

27:51.562 --> 27:55.089
(cheering, applause)

28:04.016 --> 28:07.259
♪<i> I am an old woman</i> ♪

28:07.411 --> 28:10.170
♪<i> Named after my mother</i> ♪

28:10.264 --> 28:13.598
♪<i> My old man is another</i> ♪

28:13.693 --> 28:17.111
♪<i> Child who's grown old</i> ♪

28:18.088 --> 28:20.406
♪<i> If dreams were lightning</i> ♪

28:21.349 --> 28:24.517
♪<i> And thunder were desire</i> ♪

28:24.537 --> 28:28.096
♪<i> This old house</i>
<i> would've burned down</i> ♪

28:28.098 --> 28:31.125
♪<i> A long time ago</i> ♪

28:32.044 --> 28:35.270
♪<i> Make me an angel</i> ♪

28:35.363 --> 28:38.882
♪<i> That flies from Montgomery</i> ♪

28:39.034 --> 28:41.868
♪<i> Make me a poster</i> ♪

28:41.887 --> 28:44.638
♪<i> Of an old rodeo</i> ♪

28:46.300 --> 28:49.284
♪<i> Just give me one thing</i> ♪

28:49.303 --> 28:52.788
♪<i> That I can hold on to</i> ♪

28:52.806 --> 28:55.807
♪<i> To believe in this livin'</i> ♪

28:55.901 --> 28:59.978
♪<i> Is just a hard way to go</i> ♪

29:00.130 --> 29:02.722
♪<i> To believe in this livin'</i> ♪

29:02.816 --> 29:07.327
♪<i> Is just a hard way to go.</i> ♪

29:11.733 --> 29:13.500
It's real good, Albie.

29:15.329 --> 29:17.813
I'm gonna have to wrap this up.

29:17.831 --> 29:19.815
Family is gathering

29:19.833 --> 29:21.425
for...

29:21.576 --> 29:24.319
Fake Christmas dinner tonight.

29:24.338 --> 29:27.389
Much as I'd rather be
anywhere else.

29:28.993 --> 29:31.009
Care to join us?

29:31.161 --> 29:33.161
Oh, I-I think
the Roman family's had

29:33.180 --> 29:35.522
their fill of me
for the moment, but thank you.

29:37.167 --> 29:39.485
Nicky worries about you,
you know.

29:41.338 --> 29:44.172
Well, I can't
say she's wrong to.

29:44.266 --> 29:47.993
Haven't quite been myself
since Dot passed.

29:48.862 --> 29:50.529
Holidays can be hard.

29:50.623 --> 29:51.997
Even fake ones.

29:52.792 --> 29:54.866
I never knew my father.

29:54.943 --> 29:57.853
He was out of the picture
before I was three.

29:57.855 --> 29:59.946
But it doesn't make it
any easier,

29:59.965 --> 30:01.540
especially around the holidays.

30:01.692 --> 30:03.801
What's your point, son?

30:03.952 --> 30:06.953
This Fake Christmas dinner--

30:06.972 --> 30:09.056
your family's
gonna be missing Dottie.

30:09.883 --> 30:12.309
Don't let 'em miss you, too.

30:14.496 --> 30:16.204
♪ ♪

30:16.298 --> 30:19.708
(door opens, closes)

30:19.726 --> 30:22.302
-All right.
-Right.

30:22.396 --> 30:24.046
You sure you're ready for this?

30:24.064 --> 30:25.805
Fake Christmas without Mama?

30:25.825 --> 30:28.141
Hell, it'll probably be easier
than it was<i> with</i> her.

30:28.235 --> 30:30.402
Just promise me
you'll go easier on Nicky

30:30.496 --> 30:32.888
than you did
at that Christmas set. Please.

30:32.906 --> 30:33.980
Can I ask you?

30:33.999 --> 30:36.500
Do you think
I can really do this?

30:36.727 --> 30:39.911
Become a performer
and still stay true to who I am?

30:40.064 --> 30:41.913
If anyone can, it's you.

30:42.066 --> 30:44.508
Even with two kids?

30:48.330 --> 30:49.738
-Are you serious?
-Yeah.

30:49.831 --> 30:52.015
Why not ask Luke to help us out?

30:52.242 --> 30:54.184
As much as my siblings
drive me crazy,

30:54.336 --> 30:56.687
I'd still hate for Summer
to be without one.

30:57.690 --> 30:59.598
Okay.
(squeals, laughs)

30:59.750 --> 31:01.099
(both laughing)

31:01.251 --> 31:04.361
("Jingle Bells" playing)

31:06.273 --> 31:07.105
Nellie.

31:07.199 --> 31:08.848
-Mm.
-You have been a busy bee.

31:08.868 --> 31:11.184
Have y'all seen
her new QVC commercial?

31:11.203 --> 31:13.612
I bought the entire
Nellie Bean collection.

31:13.764 --> 31:15.747
-(laughter)
-And I don't even wear lingerie.

31:15.933 --> 31:16.856
(laughter)

31:16.876 --> 31:18.208
Not often, anyway.

31:18.377 --> 31:19.618
(laughter)

31:19.712 --> 31:22.045
Thank you, sugar.
Well, I think you'd look fine

31:22.214 --> 31:26.216
in my signature
cream soda beige negligee.

31:26.326 --> 31:29.011
(chuckles softly)
It's authentic faux silk.

31:29.963 --> 31:31.796
I got something I want to say.

31:31.965 --> 31:34.132
Albie Roman giving a toast?

31:34.284 --> 31:35.800
This is a Christmas miracle.

31:35.895 --> 31:37.877
I just want to take a minute

31:37.971 --> 31:40.546
to appreciate

31:40.566 --> 31:42.882
the woman
that brought us all together.

31:42.976 --> 31:44.384
Dottie Roman made up
a fake holiday,

31:44.511 --> 31:48.071
but she did it so we'd spend
some real time together.

31:48.223 --> 31:50.132
So I hereby promise

31:50.150 --> 31:54.394
on this holy night
of Fake Christmas Eve

31:54.413 --> 31:57.639
to step up and help guide
this family into the future

31:57.658 --> 31:58.916
like Mama would've wanted.

31:59.067 --> 32:00.992
Merry Fake Christmas, everybody.

32:01.086 --> 32:02.920
-Merry Fake Christmas.
-(overlapping chatter)

32:03.147 --> 32:04.646
So, time for presents?

32:04.665 --> 32:06.757
-(chuckling)
-Unfortunately, won't be any

32:06.908 --> 32:09.167
of Dottie's homemade scarves
this year.

32:09.261 --> 32:11.486
Another Christmas miracle.

32:11.505 --> 32:15.674
(indistinct,
overlapping chatter)

32:15.826 --> 32:18.009
-For me?
-Yeah.

32:18.162 --> 32:20.753
Everybody, so...

32:20.773 --> 32:23.848
there's gonna be a new elf
on the shelf next year.

32:24.001 --> 32:25.667
We're trying for another baby.

32:25.836 --> 32:28.278
(squealing, laughter)

32:30.174 --> 32:32.007
Who's the father this time?

32:32.100 --> 32:33.784
-Luke.
-Wait, what?

32:34.011 --> 32:36.787
Just don't think about it
too hard. Just let it go.

32:36.938 --> 32:38.771
(quiet chatter)

32:38.791 --> 32:40.015
GIGI:
Thank you, Daddy.

32:40.108 --> 32:42.125
(laughter, chatter continues)

32:42.352 --> 32:44.378
-(insects trilling)
-(door opens)

32:46.281 --> 32:48.190
Merry Christmas, Uncle Luke.

32:48.208 --> 32:51.426
Doesn't quite have the same ring
as "Dad," does it?

32:52.787 --> 32:54.304
I know.

32:55.365 --> 32:57.557
But it's better this way
for everyone.

32:59.553 --> 33:01.036
Listen, I...

33:01.129 --> 33:02.646
I know
you're dealing with a lot.

33:02.815 --> 33:04.314
Mama. Clive.

33:04.466 --> 33:07.559
Now I'm gonna add
another problem to your pile.

33:07.653 --> 33:09.544
I got a call today

33:09.563 --> 33:12.472
from the assistant prosecutor
of Travis County.

33:12.491 --> 33:14.157
They want a meeting.

33:15.219 --> 33:16.735
-Why?
-The level of opiates

33:16.887 --> 33:18.478
in Mama's system.

33:18.572 --> 33:19.979
They won't let it go.

33:19.999 --> 33:21.832
-They have questions.
-Well, you tell them

33:21.983 --> 33:23.408
the truth--
that you weren't there,

33:23.485 --> 33:25.410
you don't know what happened
and you don't know who was.

33:25.562 --> 33:27.229
I'm sorry, Nick,
if I wasn't clear.

33:27.247 --> 33:29.898
The prosecutor's questions
are for you.

33:29.916 --> 33:32.134
♪ ♪

33:44.081 --> 33:45.522
-You done for the night?
-(shuts door)

33:45.673 --> 33:47.691
-Yeah.
-Mm.

33:49.194 --> 33:50.218
Mm.

33:51.179 --> 33:53.530
So you really did have
to work late.

33:54.516 --> 33:56.033
This time.

33:57.778 --> 33:58.777
You knew?

33:58.929 --> 33:59.944
Mm-hmm.

34:00.097 --> 34:01.687
I called set last night
to check on you.

34:01.765 --> 34:03.615
They told me
they released you hours ago.

34:03.767 --> 34:05.525
Ana,

34:05.544 --> 34:07.860
you're not gonna be a star
by sleeping with that boy.

34:07.954 --> 34:09.771
I didn't. Not even close.

34:09.864 --> 34:11.864
(sighs)

34:12.033 --> 34:14.468
-It's just that...
-(sighs)

34:15.962 --> 34:18.113
I know people like the Romans.

34:18.131 --> 34:20.373
They use people
and they toss them out.

34:20.392 --> 34:24.061
And I won't let them do that
to you.

34:25.064 --> 34:26.980
Do you understand?

34:28.125 --> 34:29.974
("We Wish You a Merry Christmas"
playing)

34:30.127 --> 34:32.235
(quiet chatter)

34:35.741 --> 34:37.449
DIRECTOR:
Okay, Albie. Ready.

34:37.600 --> 34:39.576
And action.

34:40.821 --> 34:42.562
Y'all may not know this,

34:42.656 --> 34:46.732
but I've never been one
for Fake Christmas

34:46.827 --> 34:49.086
or real Christmas,
for that matter.

34:49.313 --> 34:52.163
Dottie Roman changed all that.

34:52.257 --> 34:54.833
And even though she's not here
in person tonight,

34:54.927 --> 34:58.837
her spirit will be part
of this special forever.

34:58.931 --> 35:02.599
So happy holidays from us,

35:02.826 --> 35:04.342
and, like Santa,

35:04.494 --> 35:08.179
the Roman family will always be
here for you on Christmas,

35:08.332 --> 35:09.940
fake or otherwise.

